I am set up as a site administrator but I cannot get to the "Space Admin" section on spaces where I have not explicitly been given rights.  This is a problem because people create spaces and leave the permissions as default (which does not include rights for site admins to administer the space)

If you have the following markup:
{noformat}
!image.jpg|width=50%, height=50%!
{noformat}

and resize the image in the RTE and click save, you get an image with scale factors equivalent to the pixel width and height values instead.

ie. if you resized that image to 100px by 100px in the RTE, you would end up with the following markup:
{noformat}
!image.jpg|width=100%, height=100%!
{noformat}

To fix this correctly, we would need to recalculate the scale factor correctly.

At the moment, Help Tips contains the following information regarding linking:

{noformat}
Linking:
[title#anchor] » Link a page
[dev:title#anchor] » In space with 'dev'
[http://host.com] » Remote link
[phrase@shortcut] » Shortcut
Note: [alias|any_of_above_links] » Custom link title 
{noformat}

Two of the above references include reference so an anchor, yet there is no reference to creating an anchor.

We should include a line like this within the Linking section so that people can make references to Anchors work:

{noformat}
{anchor:your_anchor_name} >> Creates an anchor to which you can link to
{noformat}

After addressing that core issue, it might also be nice to include an example to link to an anchor on the same page e.g.

{noformat}
[#your_anchor_name] >> Links to anchor on same page 
{noformat}

